==English==

===Verb===
'''to [[shake]] [[off]]

# {{transitive}} To remove (something attached to, on or clinging to an object) by [[shake|shaking]].
#: ''The archaeologists '''shook off''' the dust that had fallen from the roof, and promptly continued their work.''
# {{transitive}} To disassocate oneself from (an allegation or rumour).
#: ''Some rumors that the governor had smoked pot as a teenager were flying around, but he has finally managed to '''shake''' them '''off'''.''
# {{transitive}} To lose someone who is tracking you "we managed to shake off the car following us"
#: ''The police is chasing us! Quick, turn into that side street! We've got to '''shake''' them '''off'''.''

